'association' and the 'projection of memories' 



the necessity of asking how it is first made possible by the present 
organization of Figure 2. The 'prompting' figure must take on the 
same meaning as the induced figure before it can recall it, and finally 
the de facto past is not imported into present perception by a mechan- 
ism of association, but arrayed in present consciousness itself. 



