1 We have already seen (cf. supra pp. 81-2) that the phantom limb, which is 
a modality of the body image, is understood in terms of the general movement 
of being-in-the- world. 

3 Cf. Becker, Beitrdge zur phdnomenologischen Begriindung der Geometrie und 
